# Zenithire — Company Registration & Team Management

Continues from prior modules. Expects `src/auth/`, `src/prisma/`, and
`src/notifications/` to exist. Drop in `src/companies/`, register:

```ts
import { CompaniesModule } from './companies/companies.module';

@Module({ imports: [/* ...existing */, CompaniesModule] })
export class AppModule {}
```

This is the employer-side counterpart to the admin verification endpoints
built earlier — `AdminCompaniesService.verify/reject/suspend` already
existed; this module is what actually gets a `Company` row into the
`PENDING` state for an admin to act on in the first place.

## Endpoints

| Method | Route | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| POST | `/companies` | Register a company (creates it `PENDING`, caller becomes `OWNER`) |
| GET | `/companies/me` | Your company (first membership found) |
| PATCH | `/companies/:id` | Update profile/logo — **OWNER only** |
| GET | `/companies/:id/members` | List team (OWNER or RECRUITER) |
| POST | `/companies/:id/members` | Invite an existing employer account — **OWNER only** |
| DELETE | `/companies/:id/members/:userId` | Remove a member — **OWNER only**, blocked if it would leave zero owners |

## Design notes

**Registering doesn't require anything to already exist.** Uploading a
registration document (`registrationDocUrl`) follows the same pattern as
video upload from the video module — get a presigned URL from the storage
service, upload directly, pass the resulting URL here. This module
doesn't re-implement that; it assumes the URL already exists.

**Slug collisions retry instead of failing.** Two unrelated companies
both named "Northbridge Capital" shouldn't mean the second one can't
register — `register()` appends a numeric suffix until it finds a free
slug, up to 20 attempts.

**Profile edits are OWNER-only; job posting (from the jobs module) is
any `CompanyMember`.** A recruiter you've added to help manage postings
can create and edit jobs, but can't change the company's name, logo, or
description — that distinction is deliberate, not an oversight.

**Removing the last owner is blocked.** A company can't end up with zero
owners through this endpoint — `removeMember` checks the owner count
before letting an owner remove themselves.

## What this module doesn't cover (flagged, not silent)

- **Team invite is instant, not an actual invitation flow.** Adding
  someone by email immediately grants access if they already have an
  EMPLOYER account — there's no pending-invite state, no accept/decline,
  and no path for inviting someone who doesn't have an account yet
  (that would need an invite-by-email-with-signup-link flow).
- **Notification type reuse.** The team-invite notification reuses the
  `COMPANY_VERIFIED` notification type since a dedicated `TEAM_INVITE`
  type isn't in the schema — flagged in a code comment, not hidden. Add
  the enum value if this needs to render differently in the UI.
- **Registration document review.** Admins can see a company is
  `PENDING`, but nothing here surfaces `registrationDocUrl` in a
  dedicated review UI beyond what the admin companies list already
  returns.

## Suggested next piece

Candidate profile management (education, work experience, certifications,
skills, industries CRUD + profile completion recalculation) — the
candidate-side counterpart to this module, and the last major API surface
before every screen in both dashboards is backed by real data.
